task.summary: Player is able to retrieve number of resources and victoryPoints, and check for specialCards and other types of DevelopmentCards.
PlayerTest will test if the Player class can accurately assess its own resources (e.g. when one checks if it has a number of Lumber resources)
Added Facade (for Controller interaction with model) with multiple Can-Do's. Also added jUnit package so all can create jUnit tests on classes.
Restructured DevelopmentCard, ResourceCard, and Player to use definitions shared with rest of program and modified Game to find Players
Player can find its own settlements and Game can find its players; Facade can tell if a player can build a city given a username and VertexLocation.
Added empty Test for Facade and its Can-Do methods, and implemented most of the Can-Do methods in the actual Facade class.
Modified Facade to have more clear comments, PlayerTest uses accurate functions for checking the Player class.
Added several classes for ClientModel and modified Player to fit ClientModel.
Changed Player and Facade tests to Java classes (not groovy)
Slightly modified game variables and added to my own Facade canDo Tests.
Added Controller Package with Controllers for Roll, Bank, DomesticTrade, ResourceBar_DevCard, and MaritimeTrade.
